        <num>CC 1928</num>
        <heading>1928.  Irrevocable offer</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1928.  Irrevocable offer
An offer that specifies a period of time for acceptance is irrevocable during that time.
When the offeror manifests an intent to give the offeree a delay within which to accept, without specifying a time, the offer is irrevocable for a reasonable time.</p>
        </content>
